  "discount-calc-guide": {
    "titleEn": "Discount calculator - how to calculate benefits",
    "descriptionEn": "Guide to calculating discounts. Single, double discounts, markups and real savings.",
    "contentEn": "## How to calculate the discount\n\nThe discount calculator will instantly show the final price and the actual amount of savings.\n\n## Basic calculations\n\n### Discount price\n\n**Formula:** Total price = Price × (1 - Discount/100)\n\nExample: product for 3,000 ₽ with a 25% discount → 3,000 × 0.75 = 2,250 ₽\n\n### Determining the discount percentage\n\n**Formula:** Discount = (1 - Discount Price / Original Price) × 100\n\nExample: it was 4,000 ₽, now it is 3,200 ₽ → (1 - 3200/4000) × 100 = 20%\n\n## Double and triple discounts\n\nImportant: discounts do not add up, but are multiplied!\n\n| Discounts | Apparent benefit | Real benefit |\n|--------|------------------|-----------------|\n| 20% + 10% | 30% | 28% |\n| 30% + 20% | 50% | 44% |\n| 50% + 30% | 80% | 65% |\n\n### Formula for double discount\n\nTotal discount = 1 - (1 - A/100) × (1 - B/100), where A and B are the discount amounts.\n\n## Discount vs Cashback\n\n- Discount reduces the price immediately\n- Cashback returns part of the amount later\n- With the same percentage, the discount is more profitable, since it works immediately\n\nSee also: [Interest Calculator](/tools/percentage-calc), [Tip Calculator](/tools/tip-calc)"
  },
