    "descriptionEn": "Practical examples of calculating discounts on purchases: clothing, electronics, products and services.",
    "contentEn": "## Examples of discount calculations\n\n### Seasonal clothing sale\n\nWinter jacket:\n- Original price: 15,000 ₽\n- Seasonal Sale Discount: 40%\n- Additional discount on the card: 10%\n- Total: 15,000 × 0.6 × 0.9 = 8,100 ₽\n- Real savings: 6,900 ₽ (46%)\n\n### Buying electronics\n\n| Product | Price | Discount | Total | Savings |\n|-------|------|--------|-------|----------|\n| Laptop | 85,000 ₽ | 15% | RUB 72,250 | RUB 12,750 |\n| Headphones | 12,000 ₽ | 30% | 8 400 ₽ | RUB 3,600 |\n| Case | 2,500 ₽ | 20% | 2,000 ₽ | 500 ₽ |\n| **Total** | **99 500 ₽** | — | **82 650 ₽** | **16,850 ₽** |\n\n### Product promotions\n\n“3 for the price of 2” is a 33% discount:\n- 3 packages for 200 ₽ = 600 ₽ without discount\n- On promotion: 400 ₽ (save 200 ₽)\n\n### Gym membership\n\n- Monthly payment: 4,000 ₽/month × 12 = 48,000 ₽/year\n- Annual subscription: 36,000 ₽\n- Savings: 12,000 ₽ (25%)\n\n## Conclusion\n\nAlways consider the real benefit in rubles before purchasing. The discount calculator will help you do this in a second.\n\nSee also: [Interest Calculator](/tools/percentage-calc), [Tip Calculator](/tools/tip-calc)"
